EOH, Iliad Africa, Metair, Mvelaphanda: South African Stock Market Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-03-14T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/eoh-iliad-africa-mvelaphanda-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in South Africa. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell to its lowest
since Dec. 1, sliding 295.3, or 1 percent, to 30,878.58, at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.    EOH Holdings Ltd. (EOH)  : The information technology
provider posts first-half earnings. The shares fell 24 cents, or
1.35 percent, to 17.50 rand.    Iliad Africa Ltd. (ILA)  : The producer of building
supplies reports annual earnings. The shares rose 1 cent, or 0.1
percent, to 7.01 rand.    Metair Investments Ltd. (MTA)  : The company, which
produces automobile parts, reports full-year earnings. The
shares were unchanged at 13.30 rand.    Mvelaphanda Group Ltd. (MVG)  : The commercial services
provider said it expects to report a loss per share of between
51 cents and 56 cents for the six months ended December 31,
compared with a profit of 117.3 cents per share in the year-
earlier period. It said it had entered into talks, which, if
successfully concluded, may affect its share price. The stock
rose 1 cent, or 0.3 percent, to 3.11 rand.    Sovereign Food Investments (SOV)  Ltd: The poultry
producer said its offer of shares to existing shareholders was
25 percent oversubscribed. The shares dropped 15 cents, or 2.8
percent, to 5.30 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
